                                 mork
                                 ----

                (c) Reuben Thomas 2011 <rrt@sc3d.org>
                 https://github.com/rrthomas/mork

Mork provides automatic C bindings for Lua using ctypesgen-json and
alien. (Mork is a friendly alien. However, it does not have three
eyes: the name is a shallow analogy.) Mork is distributed under the
MIT License, like Lua itself.

alien can be found at http://alien.luaforge.net/

ctypesgen-json is a fork of ctypesgen, the pure-Python wrapper
generator: http://code.google.com/p/ctypesgen/


Usage
-----

$ ctypesgen.py --all-headers --builtin-symbols --output-language=json /usr/include/foo.h -o foo.json

In Lua:

require "mork"
require "json"

module = mork.mork (json.decode (io.open ("foo.json"):read ("*a")))
